        <section id="miracle" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-blue-800">The Historical Miracle of the Oil</h2>
            <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-2xl max-w-4xl mx-auto border-t-4 border-yellow-600">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-yellow-700 mb-4">The Maccabean Revolt and the Eternal Flame</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                    Around 168 BCE, the Seleucid Greeks seized the Holy Temple and rededicated it to their gods. A small group of Jewish rebels, led by **Judah Maccabee**, reclaimed and purified the Temple. When they attempted to relight the **Menorah**, they discovered only a single jug of ritually pure olive oil—sufficient for just **one day**. Miraculously, the oil lasted for **eight days**, allowing time to produce more kosher oil. This miracle inspired the eight-day celebration of Hanukkah, symbolizing divine intervention and Jewish perseverance.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="traditions" class="mb-16 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 text-blue-800">Core Traditions: Light, Food, and Play</h2>
             <p class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-10 text-gray-600">
                The main customs tie closely to the miracle, focusing on oil and light.
            </p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
