                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-700 mb-3"><span class="font-mono text-3xl text-blue-600 mr-2">1.</span> Menorah Lighting</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Each night, a new candle is lit using the **Shammash** (helper), until all eight shine brightly on the last evening, proudly on display.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-blue-100 transition-transform transform hover:scale-105 border-b-4 border-yellow-500">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-700 mb-3"><span class="font-mono text-3xl text-blue-600 mr-2">2.</span> Oily Foods</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">To honor the oil miracle, people enjoy fried foods like **Latkes** (potato pancakes) and **Sufganiyot** (jelly donuts).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-blue-100 transition-transform transform hover:scale-105 border-b-4 border-yellow-500">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-700 mb-3"><span class="font-mono text-3xl text-blue-600 mr-2">3.</span> Dreidel Game</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">A game with a spinning top, played for **gelt** (chocolate coins), where Hebrew letters mean "A great miracle happened there."</p>
                </div>
                <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-lg border border-blue-100 transition-transform transform hover:scale-105 border-b-4 border-yellow-500">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-yellow-700 mb-3"><span class="font-mono text-3xl text-blue-600 mr-2">4.</span> Giving Gelt (Gifts)</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">The practice of gifting kids money (or chocolate coins, Gelt) fosters generosity and has grown into a nightly small-gift tradition.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
